   "source": [
    "# Chronotype Explorer — Research Notebook\n",
    "\n",
    "**Author:** Diego José Palencia Robles\n",
    "**Affiliation:** Universidad Galileo, Doctoral Program in High-Performance Administration\n",
    "**Protocol:** OSF.IO/26SCX | PRISMA-ScR | PCC Framework\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook accompanies the Streamlit application and documents the exploratory data analysis process for the scoping review on circadian rhythms, time management, and personal productivity.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "from scipy import stats\n",
    "import sqlite3\n",
    "\n",
    "sns.set_style('whitegrid')\n",
    "plt.rcParams['figure.facecolor'] = '#faf8f4'\n",
    "plt.rcParams['axes.facecolor'] = '#faf8f4'\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load data\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv('data/chronotype_data.csv')\n",
    "print(f'Loaded {len(df)} records')\n",
    "df.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Data Quality Audit\n",
    "\n",
    "Before any analysis, we verify data integrity using the same checklist from the scoping review protocol."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Check for missing values and duplicates\n",
    "print('Missing values per column:')\n",
    "print(df.isnull().sum())\n",
    "print(f'\nDuplicated rows: {df.duplicated().sum()}')\n",
    "print(f'\nData types:')\n",
    "print(df.dtypes)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Descriptive Statistics\n",
    "\n",
    "Following the protocol's data-charting variables, we compute central tendency and dispersion for all continuous variables."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "numeric_cols = ['age', 'meq_score', 'social_jetlag_hours', 'productivity_score', 'procrastination_score']\n",
    "desc = df[numeric_cols].describe().round(2)\n",
    "desc"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Hypothesis Testing\n",
    "\n",
    "**H1:** Morningness (higher MEQ) is positively correlated with productivity.\n",
    "**H2:** Social jetlag is negatively correlated with productivity.\n",
    "\n",
    "We use Pearson correlation with two-tailed significance testing (α = 0.05)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# H1: MEQ vs Productivity\n",
    "r1, p1 = stats.pearsonr(df['meq_score'], df['productivity_score'])\n",
    "print(f'H1 — MEQ vs Productivity: r = {r1:.3f}, p = {p1:.4f}')\n",
    "print(f'Result: {"Significant" if p1 < 0.05 else "Non-significant"} at α = 0.05')\n",
    "\n",
    "# H2: Social Jetlag vs Productivity\n",
    "r2, p2 = stats.pearsonr(df['social_jetlag_hours'], df['productivity_score'])\n",
    "print(f'H2 — Social Jetlag vs Productivity: r = {r2:.3f}, p = {p2:.4f}')\n",
    "print(f'Result: {"Significant" if p2 < 0.05 else "Non-significant"} at α = 0.05')\n",
    "\n",
    "# H3: Social Jetlag vs Procrastination\n",
    "r3, p3 = stats.pearsonr(df['social_jetlag_hours'], df['procrastination_score'])\n",
    "print(f'H3 — Social Jetlag vs Procrastination: r = {r3:.3f}, p = {p3:.4f}')\n",
    "print(f'Result: {"Significant" if p3 < 0.05 else "Non-significant"} at α = 0.05')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Visualization: Distribution by Work Modality\n",
    "\n",
    "Following the protocol's Context criterion, we stratify all analyses by work modality (onsite, hybrid, remote)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(15, 5))\n",
    "\n",
    "for idx, modality in enumerate(['onsite', 'hybrid', 'remote']):\n",
    "    subset = df[df['work_modality'] == modality]\n",
    "    sns.histplot(subset['social_jetlag_hours'], bins=15, kde=True, ax=axes[idx])\n",
    "    axes[idx].set_title(f'{modality.capitalize()} (n={len(subset)})')\n",
    "    axes[idx].set_xlabel('Social Jetlag (hours)')\n",
    "    axes[idx].axvline(subset['social_jetlag_hours'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.suptitle('Social Jetlag Distribution by Work Modality', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. SQL Integration\n",
    "\n",
    "Demonstrate reproducible querying against the relational database."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "conn = sqlite3.connect('data/chronotype_explorer.db')\n",
    "\n",
    "query = \"\n",
    "SELECT p.work_modality,\n",
    "       c.chronotype,\n",
    "       COUNT(*) AS n,\n",
    "       ROUND(AVG(pr.productivity_score), 2) AS avg_productivity,\n",
    "       ROUND(AVG(s.social_jetlag_hours), 2) AS avg_sjl\n",
    "FROM participants p\n",
    "JOIN chronotype_assessments c ON p.participant_id = c.participant_id\n",
    "JOIN sleep_schedules s ON p.participant_id = s.participant_id\n",
    "JOIN productivity_outcomes pr ON p.participant_id = pr.participant_id\n",
    "GROUP BY p.work_modality, c.chronotype\n",
    "ORDER BY p.work_modality, avg_productivity DESC\n",
    "\"\n",
    "\n",
    "result = pd.read_sql(query, conn)\n",
    "conn.close()\n",
    "result"
   ]
  }
 ],
